07/11/26

When all the villains are slain
or bed-ridden for life,
what evils will remain
to motivate the heros,
whose purposes live
in the heartbeat of sin?

Will we slide
into a stagnant world
that somehow measures worse
than the bitter battleground
we've so morbidly inhabited,
where unaccountable agents
run rampant with greed?

Like a dark shot of whiskey,
whose tremor snakes through
my nervous blue nerves,
and warms my worn legs,
bitingly bitter,
the death of a villain
just numbs my wild mind,
betraying the solace
I'd yearned for, for years.